                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/2310: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Munro</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-07T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >August 7, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>95. Reference my 92, August 4, 11 a.m., the Haitian Congress adjourned late
                    Wednesday night. Both Houses passed the provision conferring <pb facs="0636"
                        n="516" xml:id="pg_516"/> extraordinary financial powers upon the Government
                    but we have not yet been able obtain a final copy. The Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs assures me however that the provision will give the Government adequate
                    authority to adjust the budget so as to obtain the accord of the Financial
                    Adviser.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Munro</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
